---
/**
 * context-engineering 0006 · Figure 2 — "retrieval is the ceiling on the answer"
 * (a high-recall band vs a low-recall band).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson HTML (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the
 * footnote <sup>). Lives as an .astro component so the kebab-case SVG attributes
 * render byte-for-byte (see Fig1's header for the full rationale).
 *
 * The markers this figure references (arwR) are inlined into its own <defs>,
 * since the MDX has no shared <body> <defs> block.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 188"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A ceiling line shows generation quality is capped by retrieval recall; below the missed doc, the answer cannot recover."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="300" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >RETRIEVAL IS THE CEILING ON THE ANSWER</text
        >
        <!-- ceiling bar -->
        <rect x="40" y="36" width="520" height="30" rx="6" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="300" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >recall@k high &rarr; the answer CAN be right (model now matters)</text
        >
        <!-- floor bar -->
        <rect x="40" y="84" width="520" height="30" rx="6" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="300" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >recall@k low &rarr; relevant doc absent &rarr; answer capped, model irrelevant</text
        >
        <!-- arrow + note -->
        <line
            x1="300"
            y1="66"
            x2="300"
            y2="84"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-dasharray="4 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <text x="300" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >Everything downstream — reranking, prompting, model choice — is wasted if recall is
            low.</text
        >
        <text
            x="300"
            y="158"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#b5179e"
            >First-stage retrieval (Lesson 2) is optimized precisely for recall@k.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Retrieval sets a hard ceiling: the model can only be as right as the context allows. Grade
        it first and separately, because a strong end-answer score can still hide a chunk of hard
        queries where the relevant doc never made the top-k.<sup><a href="#s2" id="r2">2</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
